Requirements for Elevator

1. Elevator can have 3 states: Moving, Stationary, Out of order for maintenance.
2. Elevator can move in 2 directions: Down and up.
3. Door is opened only when elevator is in stationary position.
4. Internal system: user can choose the floor they wanted to go.
5. External system: Depending on the direction user wants to go, up or down button is pressd.
6. Algorithm to decide direction of elevator if more than one passenger requests for elevator.



Requirements for Elevator system:

1. Assuming total no.of floors in the building are 200
2. Assuming there are 50 elevators, 10,000 people in the building and max load as 20.